{"timestamp":"00:00:13.443","source":"Server","level":"LOG","message":"Full Signal Data: \"{\\n  \\\"title\\\": \\\"Latest AI Startup Funding News and VC Investment Deals - 2026 | News\\\",\\n  \\\"description\\\": \\\"### Matters.AI Raises $6.25 M to Safeguard Enterprise Data with AI\\\\n\\\\n   When: October 16, 2025\\\\n   Investors: Seed round co-led by Endiya Partners and Kalaari Capital, with participation from Better Capital and Carya Venture Partners (plus a $1.5 M pre-seed led by Better Capital/Carya)\\\\n   Details: Matters.AI raised $6.25 million to launch its autonomous “AI Security Engineer” which operates across devices, endpoints and environments to protect enterprise data. The company emphasises proactive and autonomous security rather than manual alerts.\\\\n   Reference:SecurityWeek\\\\n\\\\n### Resistant AI Raises $25 M Series B to Empower AI Agents Against Fraud & FinCrime\\\\n\\\\n   When: October 13, 2025\\\\n   Recipient Company: Resistant AI (Prague/Czechia-based AI models for financial crime & fraud prevention) [...] When: December 11, 2025\\\\n   Recipient Company: Runware (San Francisco-based AI inference startup)\\\\n   Investors: Led by Dawn Capital, with participation from Comcast Ventures, Speedinvest, Insight Partners, and a16z Speedrun\\\\n   Details: Runware announced $50 million in Series A funding to scale its \\\\\\\"Sonic Inference Engine,\\\\\\\" which optimizes generative AI performance. The startup aims to provide a single API that aggregates hundreds of thousands of AI models, offering significantly faster speeds and lower costs compared to traditional data center deployments. With a total of $66 million raised to date, Runware plans to expand its platform and deploy over two million models from Hugging Face by the end of 2026.\\\\n   Reference:AI Business [...] ### Defakto Raises $30 M to Secure “Non-Human” Identities\\\\n\\\\n   When: October 21, 2025\\\\n   Recipient Company: Defakto (Palo Alto/Silicon Valley-based non-human identity security startup)\\\\n   Investors: Led by XYZ Venture Capital (with participation details unlisted)\\\\n   Details: Defakto secured $30.75 million in a Series B funding round, bringing its total raised to around $50 million. The company targets non-human identity lifecycle management (machine identities, AI agents, cloud/agent footprints) with a platform focused on discovery, governance and termination of non-human identities.\\\\n   Reference:SecurityWeek\\\\n\\\\n### Gravwell Closes $15.4 M Series A to Expand Data & Security Platform\\\",\\n  \\\"url\\\": \\\"https://www.crescendo.ai/news/latest-vc-investment-deals-in-ai-startups\\\",\\n  \\\"trigger_type\\\": \\\"funding\\\",\\n  \\\"confidence_score\\\": 53,\\n  \\\"score_reasoning\\\": \\\"Notable signal based on and industry source coverage, funding, raised, investment, millions Series A Series B involving millions Series A Series B in san francisco\\\",\\n  \\\"published_date\\\": null,\\n  \\\"source\\\": \\\"crescendo.ai\\\",\\n  \\\"status\\\": \\\"new\\\",\\n  \\\"category\\\": \\\"Funding\\\",\\n  \\\"created_at\\\": \\\"2026-04-26T11:26:39.202Z\\\"\\n}\""}
