{"timestamp":"00:00:13.645","source":"Server","level":"LOG","message":"Full Signal Data: \"{\\n  \\\"title\\\": \\\"Q1 2026 Venture Capital Hits $297B: AI Captures 81 ... - Tech Insider\\\",\\n  \\\"description\\\": \\\"The Q1 2026 record rests almost entirely on four extraordinary funding rounds that collectively totaled $188 billion, accounting for roughly 63% of all global venture investment in the quarter. OpenAI’s $122 billion raise, the largest private funding round in history, valued the company at $852 billion and attracted a consortium of corporate and institutional investors. Amazon contributed approximately $50 billion, Nvidia $30 billion, and SoftBank $30 billion, with additional participation from Microsoft, Andreessen Horowitz, Sequoia Capital, Thrive Capital, Temasek, and BlackRock. [...] The table above illustrates a defining feature of Q1 2026: the near-total domination of AI and AI-adjacent companies in mega-round fundraising. Every company in the top 10 either builds foundation models, provides AI infrastructure, or deploys AI in physical systems like autonomous vehicles and military drones. Traditional software, fintech, and consumer technology startups were almost entirely absent from the billion-dollar round club.\\\\n\\\\nImage 5: Top 10 Largest Startup Funding Rounds in Q1 2026\\\\n## AI Captures 81% of All Venture Capital Dollars [...] The AI funding surge breaks down into two distinct categories. Frontier AI labs — companies building large language models and foundation models — captured the largest share, led by OpenAI, Anthropic, and xAI. AI infrastructure companies, including GPU cloud providers like CoreWeave and FluidStack, data platforms like Databricks, and chip makers like Cerebras Systems, absorbed a significant secondary share. Application-layer AI startups, those building products on top of foundation models, received comparatively modest funding.\\\",\\n  \\\"url\\\": \\\"https://tech-insider.org/q1-2026-venture-capital-297-billion-ai-startup-funding-record/\\\",\\n  \\\"trigger_type\\\": \\\"funding\\\",\\n  \\\"confidence_score\\\": 40,\\n  \\\"score_reasoning\\\": \\\"Notable signal based on and industry source coverage, funding, investment, billions involving billions\\\",\\n  \\\"published_date\\\": null,\\n  \\\"source\\\": \\\"tech-insider.org\\\",\\n  \\\"status\\\": \\\"new\\\",\\n  \\\"category\\\": \\\"Funding\\\",\\n  \\\"created_at\\\": \\\"2026-04-26T11:26:39.405Z\\\"\\n}\""}
